'''Kwak Yi-kyong''' ({{lang|ko|곽이경}}, born 1979) is a [[South Korea]]n [[LGBT]] human rights activist, civil rights activist, and labor rights activist. From 2012 to the present, she has been a representative of [[Solidarity for LGBT Human Rights of Korea]](SLRK).<ref>[http://stoo.asiae.co.kr/news/stview.htm?idxno=2013070309082876449 "동성애 부적절하다는 인식 먼저 바뀌어야"] sports today 2013-07-03 {{ko}}</ref><ref>[http://left21.com/article/13641 “혐오가 판치는 세상에는 민주주의도 없습니다”] {{ko}}</ref> 

In her early years, Kwak was involved with student movements. She was Vicechairman of [[Goryeo University]]'s Students' Union.<ref>[http://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=sec&sid1=102&oid=081&aid=0000044424 “아기업고 등교 하세요”] The Seoulnews 2005.05.28 {{ko}}</ref> In 2002, she joined [[Solidarity for LGBT Human Rights of Korea]] (SLRK). From 2004 to 2005 Kwak was Secretary General of SLRK.<ref>[http://legacy.www.hani.co.kr/section-005000000/2004/12/005000000200412101845118.html 인권위, 박형규·조준희씨에 감사패] The Hangyeorye 2004.12.10 {{ko}}</ref>

In 2005, she was appointed to Education responsible of LGBT minorities Committee (성소수자위원회) of the [[Democratic Labor Party (South Korea)|Democratic Labor Party]].<ref>[http://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=sec&sid1=102&oid=121&aid=0000001679 18~21일, ‘전쟁과 변혁의 시대’] The Prometheus 2005.08.16 {{ko}}</ref>{{huh|date=March 2014}} She was also involved with the labor rights, human rights, AIDS rights, and Anti-war peace movements. In 2011 Kwak was appointed to the LGBT minorities Committee of the [[Democratic Labor Party (South Korea)|Democratic Labor Party]].<ref>[http://www.newdaily.co.kr/news/article.html?no=97317 '다함께'의 정체는? 숙주 자살케 하는 ‘연가시’?] newdaily 2011.11.14 {{ko}}</ref> In 2013, she became adjunct policy director of the [[National Women's Union]] (전국여성노조).<ref>[http://news.khan.co.kr/kh_news/khan_art_view.html?artid=201305290600055&code=940702 <nowiki>[</nowiki>왜 지금 ‘여성 일자리’인가<nowiki>]</nowiki> 정규직 남자 중심의 노조, 주요 사안에서 여성 문제는 늘 뒷전] 경향신문 2013.05.29 {{ko}}</ref>

In 2012, she was operational chairperson (운영위원장) of SLRK. In 2013, she was chairperson of SLRK.

